task.summary: Default task
Draw map of US
First successful attempt at drawing Westchester county.
Better bounds checking for multiple features.
Get rid of files no longer needed
Added a sysman folder and additional configurations to run maintenance scripts
Remove unused files
Created radio buttons for the stations
Starting to plot points
Store maps in database
Added long island via some sysman scripts
Allow lat,lng updates from the station update page.
Show lat,lng on the statoins page via a filter.
Order the stations by the line's station order.
Add a show and remove line function to the maps.
Add a database backup of the trains mongo database.
Upgraded to WebStorm 9
Add update line so that we can change the map file.
Added TypeScript file to combine elements of two geojson files and write out a third geojson file to be used as maps in the application.
Added a floating tooltip to the map view.
Add a map that we won't use and update the tooltip to contain a link to the station.
Attempting to modularize the graphic logic
Started to pull map logic into a typescript class.
Finished port of mapping logic into a mapping class.
Pulled mapping logic out of the StationMapController
Fine tuned the display of the map in the two screens.
Move the train typescript definitions into a type definition file.
Change PlotMap return a promise so that the plot line function can be called after the map is rendered.
Fix the controllers to use the PlotMap promise.
Make the mapfile choice a lookup
Trying to improve the form layout.
Added another dump of the mongo train database since I just added a lot of stations for the Hudson line with their correct geo coordinates.
Starting to refactor the Maps module to handle both Line and Train plotting.
Expand the Maps module to plot the map for either a line or a train. In the case of a train, more than one map may be combined so that all stops can be shown across lines.
Add a directive to allow mouse over events to trigger the station select behavior.
Add mouse enter and leave behaviors to trigger an expanding circle and the tooltip to be placed by the station.
Provide a call back mechanism when you click a station on a map
Redraw train map on station delete
Total redo of the layout of the train details page. Eliminated the station list in order to use the map to select stations.
Create blackout stops on the line map to indicate stops already on the given trains route.

When displaying a train, automatically select the line (and draw its map) that corresponds to the line of the last stop. If the last stop is on multiple lines, just pick the first line in which it is found. Added hover behavior to the stop list to bring up the floating tooltip for the station on the map.
Add methods to display and remove station labels.
Add some CSS transitioning when we zoom the map.
More transition fun
Text change for the home page
Show a map of a trip
Add the ability to find a bounding box for the map based on the features that contain the supplied stations.
Allow a callback for label text. Trip controller uses it to label the stops with the station name and stop time.
Optionally label the geographic features with their names
Completed new poi form and api method.
